observations.recommendation:
We recommended and
Management agreed to the
following:
a. The BAC see to it that invitations are sent to various observers five days before the conduct of the eligibility checking, shortlisting, pre-bid conference, preliminary examination of bids, bid evaluation and post qualification. Said invitations should be properly filed and attached together with the contracts submitted so that the team will be able to determine management’s compliance with the said promulgation;
b. The BAC submit complete detailed engineering documents for the above contracts under review. Henceforth, Management perform detailed engineering activities before the conduct of any bidding;
c. Management submit the lacking technical documents listed in item 13.14, if any, for evaluation;
d. The BAC submit the required performance security for contracts listed in Item 13.17, if any. Henceforth, the BAC sees to it that future winning bidders post the required performance security before the contract signing.
e. The BAC submit the DOLE approved CHSP for all contracts, if any. Henceforth, the BAC require the contractors to submit a DOLE approved CHSP prior to the contract signing. Non-compliance shall cause the disqualification of the contractor;
f. The BAC submit lacking documents listed in Item 13.27. Henceforth, BAC see to it that documents required in Sec. 37.2.3 of the Revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184 form part of the contract; and
g. The BAC henceforth adhere to the transparency provisions as provided by the regulations cited in Sections 37.1 and 37.4 of the same IRR.

