observations.recommendation:
We have recommended that in order to establish accurately and reliably the balances of local road networks and the related existence and condition thereof, the management undertake the following:
The Municipal Engineer and the members of Inventory Committee conduct a yearly physical count of local road network projects and consequently submit a result of inventory following the format prescribed in COA Circular 2015-008 as well as update the local road map of the LGU;
The Municipal Engineer provide the Municipal Accountant and the Property Custodian the description and cost segregation of road components of various road infrastructure projects;
The Municipal Accountant keeps and maintain subsidiary ledger for roads and its components and reconcile the same to the result of the physical count at the end of each year.

In view of the noted discrepancies between the records of the LGU and other government agencies, we have recommended the following:
The Municipal Accountant and Treasurer reconcile their record with the GSIS, PAG-IBIG and PHILHEALTH;
Henceforth, the Municipal Accountant and Treasurer regularly reconcile their quarterly financial records with the records of other government agencies.

In view of the above noted lapses, we have recommended the following:
The MPDC/MENRO sees to it that henceforth, all relevant cost for the implementation of the SWMP is integrated to the Annual Budget as well as Annual Investment Plan. Coordination among the different offices is hereby advised;
The Municipal Mayor convenes the SWMB and seeks justification as to the reason for the low success rate for the implementation of SWM projects;
The members of the SWMB revisit the provisions of the IRR of R.A. No. 9003. Henceforth, implement quality assurance/ monitoring mechanism to facilitate an efficient and effective implementation of the programs indicated in the SWMP

We have recommended the following:
 The Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer install effective internal control on the municipality’s collection system including controls for the issuances, reporting, monitoring and safeguard of all accountable forms of the municipality;
 The Municipal Treasurer properly verify the Reports of Collections and Deposits of all collectors and monitor issuances and balances of accountable forms. Check the Statement of Accountable Forms as to initial balances on hand, receipts, issues and the ending balances on hand and make a physical count of accountable forms remaining in the custody of the collectors and check against ending balances on hand column; 
 The Municipal Treasurer to issue new set of accountable forms to the collectors only when the previously issued accountable forms are fully issued and properly reported in the RCDs; and
 The Municipal Treasurer to present all the unaccounted accountable forms and submit the same to the Office of the Auditor for verification.
